Running the Projects
Mobile App
bash
yarn mobile
Web App
bash
yarn web
Key Technologies

React Native
Gatsby
NativeWind (Tailwind CSS for React Native)
Monorepo with Yarn Workspaces

Transpilation Approach

Uses Babel to transpile React Native components for web
NativeWind provides cross-platform styling
Module resolver helps with imports across packages

Configuration Notes

metro.config.js handles React Native module resolution
gatsby-config.js sets up transpilation for React Native modules
Babel configs enable cross-platform component sharing

Troubleshooting

Ensure all dependencies are installed
Check that Babel and module resolution configs are correct
Verify React Native and React Native Web versions are compatible

Adding New Shared Components

Create components in apps/shared/src/components
Export from apps/shared/src/index.js
Import in mobile or web apps using @george-barbu-es/shared